UAT TESTING PLAN

Testers: 
Kian, Arman, Riley, Reed run locally from github clone instance
Peer reviewers on a deployed website



Test 1: Valid user registration and account creation 
ENVIORNMENT: 
Localhost
Server: Node.js
Database: PostgreSQL local instance 

Test that a user is directed accordingly and shown a proper account creation message

A user must fulfil the regex requirements for email and password when using the register page
A valid email, some string of letters followed by an @ symbol, and a domain must be provided
A valid password must be provided that fulfills the requirements listed

Input:
feizjkian@gmail.com
Password: ThisIsATest23
Expected Result:
The server navigates the user to the home page
The server tells the user that an account was successfully created
The server stores the new user data in the users database 

Test 2: Invalid user registration with bad input
ENVIORNMENT: 
Localhost
Server: Node.js
Database: PostgreSQL local instance 
Test that users put in correctly formatted data that can be inserted into the USERS table

A user fails to submit one of the dedicated forms:
Email
Password

INPUT:
Input:
Email: ThisIsATest
Password: hi (under character limit)

Expected Result:
No data is inserted into the users table
User receives an error message that correctly reflects the failed input
User is not directed or removed from the register page

Test 3: Valid route storage within a users account
ENVIORNMENT: 
Localhost
Server: Node.js
Database: PostgreSQL local instance Tests that a user inputted route they wish to take via the bus is possible and will be properly inserted into a routes table

A user plots a route on the homepage from one location to another
A user clicks a dedicated save button

INPUT:
Click on Boulder Campus
Click on DIA


Expected result:
A user receives a valid route and is shown bus times for their respective journey
A user's route is properly inserted into a routes table
A user's route is kept even after logout
A user's saved routes are properly shown on button click

Data description: 
Check that location data is stored, specifically 
